# DeepL API Key (Free or Pro)
# Sign up at https://www.deepl.com/pro-api
DEEPL_API_KEY=your-deepl-api-key-here
# Spring Boot doesn't automatically load .env files — it only reads system environment variables. You might wanna run export DEEPL_API_KEY=your-deepl-api-key-here in the terminal before starting the application, or you can set it in your IDE's run configuration.